# Appendix F — Cortex integration cookbook

Patterns for storing state and reading it back.

## Recipe 1 — remember a fact

Write a `cortex-slice` with a small value.

```sakura-scheme
(cortex-write! 'kid.alfred.favorite-color 'blue)
```

Read it back later:

```sakura-scheme
(cortex-read 'kid.alfred.favorite-color)
```

Returns `'blue`. Persisted forever until you overwrite.

## Recipe 2 — remember a structured record

The value can be any legal slat.

```sakura-scheme
(cortex-write! 'kid.alfred.first-cart
  '(cart-info :id \"cart-my-paddle\"
              :first-run #inst \"2026-07-11T14:32:00Z\"
              :atoms-learned (score-var mutation)))
```

Read:

```sakura-scheme
(define info (cortex-read 'kid.alfred.first-cart))
(slat-key info 'atoms-learned)
```

Returns `(score-var mutation)`.

## Recipe 3 — append to a stream

For anything that happens over time — events, mood changes, chat
turns — use a `.slatl` stream, not a single slice.

```sakura-scheme
(cortex-append! 'sakura.mood
  (list 'event :ts (now) :kind :mood.changed :to :focused))
```

Read the stream:

```sakura-scheme
(define events (cortex-stream 'sakura.mood))
(for-each display-mood events)
```

## Recipe 4 — snapshot + delta timeline

For state that changes gradually — session progress, cart state — use
snapshots plus deltas.

```sakura-scheme
(define (checkpoint! subject state)
  (cortex-write!
    (symbol-append subject '.snapshot)
    (list 'snapshot :ts (now) :subject subject :body state)))

(checkpoint! 'sakura.session
  '(session :active #t :queue-depth 3 :last-user 'alfred))
```

Between snapshots, write deltas:

```sakura-scheme
(cortex-append! 'sakura.session-deltas
  (list 'delta
        :from-ts (previous-ts)
        :to-ts   (now)
        :changes '((queue-depth 3 -> 5))))
```

## Recipe 5 — verify before load

For state coming from disk, verify the signature before trusting.

```sakura-scheme
(define slice (read-slice-from-disk 'kid.alfred.programs))
(if (slat-verify slice :public-key sakuras-public-key)
    (slat-key slice 'value)
    (error \"cortex slice signature failed\"))
```

## Recipe 6 — encrypt at rest

For sensitive slices — private thoughts, per-user secrets — encrypt.

```sakura-scheme
(define plaintext '(private-notes \"...text...\"))

(define slice
  (list 'cortex-slice
        :key 'kid.alfred.private
        :encrypted (encrypt-bytes (slat-dumps plaintext) session-key)
        :encrypted-algo \"xchacha20-poly1305\"
        :key-hint \"kid-2026\"
        :owner 'sakura
        :ts (now)))

(cortex-write-slice! slice)
```

Read:

```sakura-scheme
(define slice (cortex-read-slice 'kid.alfred.private))
(define plaintext-bytes
  (decrypt-bytes (slat-key slice 'encrypted) session-key))
(slat-loads (bytes->string plaintext-bytes))
```

## Recipe 7 — persona-continuity snapshot

For \"restore Sakura's session next time she opens,\" snapshot her whole
state at session-end and restore at session-start.

```sakura-scheme
(define (save-session)
  (cortex-write! 'sakura.last-session
    (list 'snapshot :ts (now) :subject 'sakura.session
          :body (list
                  (list 'mood     current-mood)
                  (list 'user     current-user)
                  (list 'queue    current-queue)
                  (list 'last-cart current-cart)))))

(define (restore-session)
  (let ([snap (cortex-read 'sakura.last-session)])
    (when snap
      (let ([body (slat-key snap 'body)])
        (set! current-mood     (cadr (assoc 'mood     body)))
        (set! current-user     (cadr (assoc 'user     body)))
        (set! current-queue    (cadr (assoc 'queue    body)))
        (set! current-cart     (cadr (assoc 'last-cart body)))))))
```

At session-start, `restore-session`. At session-end, `save-session`.

## Recipe 8 — content-addressed dedup

If the value is an atom (training material, incident narrative), key
it by content ID instead of a human-readable key.

```sakura-scheme
(define atom
  '(atom :id \"atm-scheme-lambda-001\" :body '(lambda (x) x)))

(define cid (slat-cid atom))

(cortex-write! (symbol-append 'atom.by-cid. cid) atom)
```

Two writers producing the same atom store it once. Dedup for free.

## Recipe 9 — trim old snapshots

Storage is finite. Trim old snapshots on a schedule.

```sakura-scheme
(define (trim-snapshots subject keep-count)
  (let* ([keys (cortex-keys-with-prefix (symbol-append subject '.snapshot))]
         [sorted (sort keys > by-timestamp)]
         [to-drop (drop sorted keep-count)])
    (for-each cortex-delete! to-drop)))

(trim-snapshots 'sakura.session 100)
```

Keeps the 100 most recent snapshots. Drops the rest.

## Recipe 10 — search a stream

Use a filter over the stream.

```sakura-scheme
(define recent-moods
  (filter (lambda (event)
            (equal? (slat-key event 'kind) :mood.changed))
          (cortex-stream 'sakura.events)))

(take recent-moods 10)
```

Or use Loam projections if the stream is big — Loam pre-projects the
common queries.

